      <h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

      <p>
        This disclosure is provided in accordance with the United States
        Federal Trade Commission's guidelines on endorsements and
        testimonials (16 CFR, Part 255) and equivalent consumer-protection
        rules in other jurisdictions.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate relationships</h2>
      <p>
        The Life Insider participates in various affiliate marketing
        programs. This means we may earn commissions on purchases made
        through links from our site to retailers and brands, including but
        not limited to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Amazon Associates.</strong> As an Amazon Associate, The
          Life Insider earns from qualifying purchases. Amazon, Amazon Prime,
          the Amazon logo and Amazon Prime logo are trademarks of Amazon.com,
          Inc. or its affiliates.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Direct brand and network partnerships</strong>, where we
          earn a commission or referral fee when you purchase from a featured
          brand through our links.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What this means for you</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Clicking our links never increases the price you pay.</li>
        <li>You are never obligated to use our links.</li>
        <li>
          Commissions fund our research and keep the site free to use. They
          can influence which products we feature and where they appear —
          they do not change a product's Insider Score. See
          <a href="/how-we-rate/">How We Rate</a> and our
          <a href="/advertising-disclosure/">Advertising Disclosure</a> for
          full details.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Questions</h2>
      <p>
        If anything here is unclear, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>
        — we'll gladly explain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
